      <abstract id="aspace_9f8ccac0ba1a995af93b3a0627110484">David Giannini is an American poet who has published more than 30 collections with small presses, and whose work has appeared in national and international literary magazines and anthologies. <emph render="italic">Opens</emph>, his first book of poetry, was published in 1971 by Genesis: Grasp Press, which he edited and co-founded in 1967. The David Giannini Collection on Richard Hell and Genesis: Grasp (dated 1968-1972) consists of correspondence between Richard Hell and Giannini, the majority of which consists of letters from Hell.</abstract>
      <physloc id="aspace_53b1ea3bf5e4067dd5374a8dd6ffb7c6">Materials are stored offsite and advance notice is required for use. Please request materials at least two business days prior to your research visit to coordinate access.</physloc>
