    <scopecontent id="aspace_daa815af0c1e986d071e8f3df343b10c">
      <head>Scope and Contents</head>
      <p>The David Giannini Collection on Richard Hell and Genesis: Grasp (dated 1968-1972) consists of correspondence between Richard Hell and David Giannini, an early collaborator on projects such as the poetry journal <emph render="italic">Genesis: Grasp</emph>. The majority of the collection consists of letters from Hell.</p>
    </scopecontent>
    <bioghist id="aspace_52669f1eec7a272a9903959c910f45df">
      <head>Biographical Note</head>
      <p>David Giannini (born 1948) is an American poet who has published more than 30 collections with small presses, and whose work has appeared in national and international literary magazines and anthologies. <emph render="italic">Opens</emph>, his first book of poetry, was published in 1971 by Genesis: Grasp Press, which he edited and co-founded in 1967.</p>
    </bioghist>
